f received a ba from johns hopkins university and an mba from new york university in  barely out of college scharf was the youngest professional employee at commercial credit corp the first person the company had hired directly from college in years scharf was in fact still a senior at johns hopkins university when he started working there parttime having sent his résumé to jamie dimon through family connections six months into the job he was named dimon’s assistant and “included in every meeting learning broadly about business and how decisions get made as much as scharf has been mentored by the leading lights of his industry he has developed a philosophy of his own in part that was shaped by his executive mba from stern which he completed in  and he said helped put his work experience into perspective “in my experience” he reflected “good business is all about stepping back asking questions and accumulating the expertise to make the best decisions whether those are business decisions or people decisions early careeredit prior to joining visa in november of  scharf was the ceo of retail financial services for jpmorgan chase  co for nine years from july  until june of  he was also the managing director of one equity partners jpmorgans private investment section he was the ceo and cfo at bank one corp prior to his work at jpmorgan chase  co from  to  from  to  he was the cfo of the global corporate and investment bank division at citigroup inc from  to  he was the cfo at salomon smith barney he began his career as mr dimons assistant at commercial credit in the late s careeredit scharf at age  took over as the companys ceo in november  succeeded joseph saunders he was also appointed as a board member after increasing the size of the board to eleven members from ten he has more than  years of financial services payments systems and leadership experience he was also a director of visa and its predecessor visa usa from  to  payments technology company visa inc v revealed in a regulatory filing on friday that chief executive officer charles scharf received a  total compensation of  million including base salary stock grants and incentives in  scharf is earning praise from analysts and insiders for breaking with tradition he has made visa no  on the fortune  with  billion in revenue more open to merchants and tech innovation he oversees a network with  billion cards accepted by  million merchants globally and he has done it with little flash he mostly avoids press sources describe him as “allbusiness” nonprofit leadershipedit scharf is on the board of trustees for johns hopkins university and he is on the board of directors for the financial services roundtable on february   president barack obama announced his intent to nominate individuals to key administration posts amongst which was charles w scharf appointee for member president’s advisory council on financial capability for young americans he is currently on the executive council for ucsf health and the board of directors for microsoft corp on october   scharf advised his board of directors that he can no longer spend enough time in san francisco to do the job effectively he announced that he would step down on december httpswwwreuterscomarticleusvisamovesceoiduskbnhev referencesedit  gardner sean visa hires jpmorgans charles scharf as ceo reuters retrieved  october    a b c charles scharf forbes retrieved  october    fast track to success wsternnyuedu  retrieved    a b roberts daniel charles scharf visas openarmed leader fortune retrieved  october    sidel robin visa swipes boss from jp morgan the wall street journal retrieved  october    visa ceo charles scharf gets total compensation of  mln in  rttnewscom  retrieved   retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlecharlesscharfoldid categories  birthsamerican chief executives of financial services companiesamerican businesspeoplejohns hopkins university alumniliving peoplestern school of business alumni navigation menu pe